---
description: Prompt template guidance for workflow-oriented tasks
alwaysApply: true
---

## When to suggest templates
- New project setup: suggest the `Nuevo proyecto` template when the user asks to initialize a repo or start a new SaaS/app.
- New feature implementation: suggest the `Iniciar feature nueva` template when the user names a feature and mentions related files/constraints.
- Debugging: suggest the `Debug — algo no funciona` template when the user reports a bug or error and provides expected/actual behavior.
- Explaining code: suggest the `Entender código ajeno` template when the user asks to understand existing code.
- Refactoring: suggest the `Refactoring` template when the user requests readability/perf/DRY/error-handling improvements with scope constraints.
- Code review: suggest the `Code review rápido` template when the user asks for correctness/security-focused review.
- Writing tests: suggest the `Escribir tests` template when the user requests new tests or test coverage.
- New API endpoints: suggest the `Nuevo endpoint de API` template when the user wants an endpoint added/modified.
- Security review: suggest the `Revisar seguridad` template when the user requests a security pass.
- Preparing to ship: suggest the `Preparar para ship` template when the user references shipping/release gates.

## Template skeletons (copyable prompt formats)

### Initialize project (`Nuevo proyecto`)
```text
Initialize this project as [DESCRIBE TU SAAS EN 1-2 LÍNEAS].
Use my hono-template structure from github.com/Butrelo8/hono-template.
Update package.json name, README, and .env.example with the correct project details.
Create TODOS.md, DECISIONS.md, BUGS.md, and CHANGELOG.md if they don't exist.
```

### Implement feature (`Iniciar feature nueva`)
```text
I want to implement [NOMBRE DE LA FEATURE].

Context:
- Stack: Hono + Bun backend, Next.js frontend, PostgreSQL + Drizzle
- Related files: [ARCHIVOS RELEVANTES O "search the codebase first"]
- Constraints: [LIMITACIONES O "none"]

Before implementing:
1. Search the codebase for similar patterns
2. Tell me what already exists that we can reuse
3. Propose the minimal implementation — fewest files, fewest abstractions
4. Wait for my approval before writing any code
```

### Debug (`Debug — algo no funciona`)
```text
I have a bug.

File/function: [ARCHIVO O FUNCIÓN]
Expected: [QUÉ DEBERÍA PASAR]
Actual: [QUÉ ESTÁ PASANDO]
Error message: [PEGA EL ERROR COMPLETO O "none"]

Rules:
- Search the codebase before suggesting a fix
- Do NOT reformat code outside the scope of the fix
- Fix the root cause, not just the symptom
- If you need more context, ask — don't assume
```

### Understand code (`Entender código ajeno`)
```text
Explain this code as if I'm an intermediate developer.

Cover:
1. What it does in plain English
2. Why it's written this way (patterns used)
3. What could go wrong or break
4. Anything I should change or improve

Use Context7 if it references any external library.
Do not rewrite anything — explain only.
```

### Security review (`Revisar seguridad`)
```text
Do a security review of [ARCHIVO O "this entire codebase"].

Check for:
- Hardcoded secrets or API keys
- Missing input validation or sanitization
- SQL injection vectors
- Auth bypass possibilities
- Sensitive data exposed in logs or responses
- Missing rate limiting on public endpoints

Be specific — cite file:line for each issue.
```
